ObjectDataImport.name: ObjectDataImport
ObjectDataImport.description: Represents the data import status of one or more object records.

EndDate.description: The date and time (in UTC) when the data import finished.

FileName.description: Optional. If the data import was from a comma-delimited file (CSV), the name of the file. The maximum length is 120 characters.

ObjectDataImportNumber.description: An auto-generated number identifying the data import.

OwnerId.description: The ID of the user who owns the data import status record.

PrimaryObject.description: The name of the primary object being imported. For example, Lead. This value is usually provided programmatically. The maximum length is 120 characters.

Result.description: The JSON response of the data object import result, including error messages.

Status.description: The processing status of the data object import.

Type.description: The type of data import, such as from a comma-delimited file or through a connector.
